outbreak.info R package

July 16, 2020

getExactLocations

Description:

Get iso3 codes for a country, state/province, county, and/or metro area.

Usage:

getExactLocations(locations_to_search)

Arguments:

locations_to_search: a vector or list of location (country, state/province, county, metro area) names

Example:

iso3=getExactLocations(c("Texas", "Brazil", "San Diego County"))
print(iso3)
## [1] "BRA"             "USA_US-CA_06073" "USA_US-TX"

getExactNames

Description:

Get exact spelling of locations at the same administrative level.

Usage:

getExactNames(locations_to_search, admin_level)

Arguments:

locations_to_search: a vector or list of location names at the same administrative level

admin_level: an integer representing an administrative level (countries = 0, states/provinces = 1, metro areas = 1.5, counties = 2)

Example:

names=getExactNames(c("California", "Florida", "Texas"), admin_level=1)
print(names)
## [1] "Florida"    "California" "Texas"

getAdmn2Data

Description:

Retrieve a dataframe of up-to-date COVID-19 data from outbreak.info for all counties in a state or states.

Usage:

getAdmn2Data(states_of_interest)

Arguments:

states_of_interest: a vector or list of state names

Example:

countydf=getAdmn2Data("California")
print(unique(countydf$name))

plotCases

Description:

Plot cases using up-to-date COVID-19 cases using data from outbreak.info for location(s) of interest (country, state/province, county, metro area)

Usage:

plotCases(locs)

Arguments:

locs: a vector or list of location(s) of interest

Example:

plotCases(c("Texas", "Brazil", "San Diego County"))

plotCasesPer100k

Description:

Plot cases using up-to-date COVID-19 cases per 100,000 using data from outbreak.info for location(s) of interest (country, state/province, county, metro area)

Usage:

plotCasesPer100k(locs)

Arguments:

locs: a vector or list of location(s) of interest

Example:

plotCasesPer100k(c("Texas", "Brazil", "San Diego County"))
